cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the evaluation of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on a visual perception task, specifically the Gestalt principle of closure. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses the challenges faced by state-of-the-art CNNs in perceiving objects based on this principle, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also evaluates the performance of the networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the human perception of visual elements, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category.
